The south-central black rhinoceros (Diceros bicornis minor) or  south-central hook-lipped rhinoceros is a subspecies of the black rhinoceros.  In line with the rules of zoological nomenclature, the South-central black rhinoceros should be known as Diceros bicornis keitloa (Smith, 1836), a nomen novum.
Although it was the most numerous of the black rhino subspecies it is still listed as critically endangered by the IUCN red list. Like other black rhino subspecies it has a prehensile lip and lives in savanna habitat.